Sentencas: A performance of an anode-supported tubular Ni-8YSZ/Ni-ScSZ/ScSZ/GDC/LSC cell was investigated at 650-750 degrees C by feeding model kerosene reformate gas (H-2, H2O, CO, CO2, and CH4) to a Ni-8YSZ/Ni-ScSZ anode.
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas

Sentencas: Variations of gas composition were observed not only between inlet and outlet of anode to estimate the degree of internal reforming, but also during current input by online quadrupole mass spectrometry and Fourier-transform infrared spectrometry.
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the cell was independent of reforming temperature of kerosene, i.e. gas composition (in particular CH4 concentration) at moderate anode gas flow rates.
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas

Sentencas: At open-circuit states, 10% or less methane in the kerosene-reformed gas was readily converted by steam or CO, over the Ni-8YSZ/Ni-ScSZ electrode so that gas compositions could almost follow the thermodynamic equilibrium at 650-750 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas

Sentencas: This suggests that the internal reforming should proceed almost completely over the Ni anode.
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas

Sentencas: Consumption of H, and CO and production of CO, were observed during current input.
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas

Sentencas: I-V characteristics remained constant at 650 degrees C as long as anodic W/F was more than 0.2 kg mmol(-1)
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas
Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas

Sentencas: It was demonstrated that a catalytic activity of an anode electrode for hydrocarbons will be important for SOFCs with liquid fuels such as kerosene in order not to deteriorate cell perfonnance.
Titulo: Performance of a tubular solid oxide fuel cell with model kerosene reformate gas
